name: A Floral Affair Necklace
description:
Perfect for any occasion, although it would make a great statement necklace for your wedding day!

This piece is made up of several different vintage elements including two sets of clip-on earrings and two flower pins.

The main focal point and the two highest flowers are a completed vintage set including a pin and two clip-on earrings. The two middle points consist of an multi-floral pin, and a large single flower pin. All vintage elements included on this piece are Coro vintage jewelry.

These vintage elements no longer function for their prior use, therefore they can no longer be used as earrings or pins but instead have been redefined and transformed into this stunning statement necklace that can be worn with practically anything.

This necklace can be dressed down for everyday wear or be dressed up elegantly enough to be "something old" you wear for your wedding day! This piece really is a hidden treasure and it will easily turn into one of your favorite items in your jewelry box!

name: Joys of Spring Necklace
description:
A beautiful combination of vintage elements brought together into a unique and sensational conversation piece! This necklace would catch anyone's eye! 

This necklace is made of a set of vintage clip-on earrings and a pin that contain little sky blue enamel flowers! Additional elements include a pin that takes the shape of a leaf with sky blue, grass green and foggy white rhinestones and clip-on earrings adorning the framing of your neck that share similar colors and style to the leaf pin.

These vintage elements no longer function for their prior use, therefore they can no longer be used as earrings or pins but instead have been redefined and transformed into this stunning statement necklace that can be worn with practically anything.

All my re-purposed vintage jewelry is made with vintage components dating back as far as 60 years! So they have stories, personalities, and character of their own. These are not things you will find at a store, they are special and unique. 

This necklace can be dressed down for everyday wear or be dressed up elegantly enough to be "something old" you wear for your wedding day! This piece really is a hidden treasure and it will easily turn into one of your favorite items in your jewelry box!

Due to the weight of the item, shipping will be more expensive on vintage re-purposed pieces. If you would like tracking included in your shipping please let me know.

name: Queen of Hearts Necklace
description:
This piece is a statement necklace that could turn the heads of anyone in a crowd. The necklace is comprised of vintage components as well as floral cabochons. The cabochons are both red and are different sizes. To the left (in picture) of the main focal flower is a rhinestone vintage crown pin (a David crown pin) (research it - it's amazing!), displaying various colors. These crown pins are hard to find in the vintage or flea market world today and are a real gem! To the right (in picture) of the main focal flower is a vintage bug pin that resembles a bee, he is gold in color and has luminescent rhinestones throughout his wings. At the top of each side of the necklace is a matching pair of vintage clip on earrings in red, they also contain luminescent multicolored rhinestones as well that compliment the crown. The backing of all of these vintage elements has been removed to provide a more fluent and formatted look to the necklace, this allows the necklace to lay even on your chest and show off each piece evenly.

Thank you for looking! This is part of my spring collection for 2013 and I am very excited about it!
